Class IdentVsRealTableDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container

          • java.awt.Dialog

              • com.cafean.client.ui.IdentVsRealTableDialog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
    public class IdentVsRealTableDialog
extends javax.swing.JDialog
    This table is used to edit tables of ident references vs real values. The model, idents, Real values and category must be set before the dialog is set visible. This can be done in the optional constructor or individually using the set functions.

        public IdentVsRealTableDialog​(java.awt.Frame parent,
                              int[] idents,
                              Real[] reals,
                              Category category,
                              AbstractModel model)
        Creates a new IdentVsRealTableDialog, and passes in all the important data.
        Parameters:
        parent - the java.awt.Frame that spawned this dialog.
        idents - the integer array of ident references to components.
        reals - the Real array. This should be of the type of the Real being edited.
        category - the Category of the components.
        model - the current AbstractModel.
